**Task 1: Basin-scale versus whole-sheet trends.**

The whole-Antarctic trend masks large regional contrasts. The East Antarctic Ice Sheet (EAIS, roughly $0^\circ$ to $180^\circ$ E) has been close to mass balance or slightly gaining; the West Antarctic Ice Sheet (WAIS, roughly $-140^\circ$ to $-60^\circ$ E) has been losing mass rapidly, driven by the glaciers draining the Amundsen Sea sector. Adapt `ewh_to_Gt` to extract EAIS and WAIS separately using bounding boxes, fit trends to each, and compare the basin trends with the continental sum. Is the WAIS loss rate consistent with what the input-output method finds for Pine Island and Thwaites? (You will need the discharge numbers from {doc}`insar`.)

